ntral part. The rotation of\na gas halo is found to make SFR lower in the model. The SFRs in the runs\nincluding galactic winds are found to be lower than the same runs but without\nwinds. We conclude that the effects of a hot gaseous halo on the evolution of\ngalaxies are generally too significant to be simply ignored, and expect that\nmore hydrodynamical processes in galaxies could be understood through numerical\nsimulations employing both gas disk and gas halo components.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 30 Dec 2012 13:49:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-18"}
