{"id":"1301.1284","submitter":"Robert R. Tucci","authors":"Robert R. Tucci","title":"Maxwell Demon from a Quantum Bayesian Networks Perspective","comments":"30 pages (6 files: 1 .tex, 2 .sty, 3 .eps)","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We propose a new inequality that we call the conditional ageing inequality\n(CAIN). The CAIN is a slight generalization to non-equilibrium situations of\nthe Second Law of thermodynamics. The goal of this paper is to study the\nconsequences of the CAIN. We use the CAIN to discuss Maxwell demon processes\n(i.e., thermodynamic processes with feedback.) In particular, we apply the CAIN\nto four cases of the Szilard engine: for a classical or a quantum system with\neither one or two correlated particles. Besides proposing this new inequality\nthat we call the CAIN, another novel feature of this paper is that we use\nquantum Bayesian networks for our analysis of Maxwell demon processes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 30 Dec 2012 07:56:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-01-08"}
